<task id="011" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-11 Wire `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools()` to Read `sprk_analysistool` Rows (Pillar 2)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>010</dependencies>
    <blocks>012, 020, 024</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, chat</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies chat-agent core tool-resolution path; NFR-01 conversational primacy bound; downstream blocker for batch migration + facade tasks; tags `bff-api`+`ai`+`chat`.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent file; gates downstream but no contention.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Replace `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools()` hardcoded tool-class wiring with a
    data-driven query: read `sprk_analysistool` rows where `AvailableInContexts ∋ "Chat"`
    (task 007 enum value Chat or Both), wrap each row + corresponding `IToolHandler` impl
    via `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` (task 010), and return the resulting
    `AIFunction[]` to the chat-agent build.

    Critical-path context: this task is the chat-side cutover for Pillar 2. Once it lands,
    adding a Dataverse row exposes a new tool to the LLM next request — no code deploy
    needed. Task 012 (batch migration) populates rows for the 10 pre-R5 chat tools. Tasks
    020 (invoke_playbook facade) and 024 (FK fix) depend on this wiring.

    BACKWARD COMPAT during migration: existing hardcoded tool classes (DocumentSearch,
    AnalysisQuery, etc.) MUST continue to work during the Phase A migration window. The
    factory MAY retain the hardcoded list as a feature-gated fallback during task
    011-to-012 transition (gated by EXISTING capability flag — NO new feature flag per
    ADR-018). Document the migration cutover plan in task notes.

    NFR-01 binding: even with the new data-driven tool list, the LLM's conversational
    ability is NEVER suppressed. Tool list is what's exposed for function-calling; the
    underlying LLM still responds conversationally to every turn. Safety pipeline preserved
    per NFR-13.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with `SprkChatAgentFactory` + `ResolveTools()` expertise. Familiar
    with Dataverse query patterns + NFR-01 conversational primacy contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools()` reads `sprk_analysistool` rows with
    `AvailableInContexts ∋ "Chat"`, wraps via adapter, returns `AIFunction[]` to chat-agent.
    Existing hardcoded tools continue to work during migration via feature-gated fallback
    (existing flag, no new flag). Build green; publish-size delta reported; NFR-01
    conversational regression test green.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="factory">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
    <file purpose="adapter">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter.cs</file>
    <file purpose="chat-architecture">docs/architecture/chat-architecture.md</file>
    <file purpose="bff-claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">No new top-level Program.cs lines; query service if needed registered inside `AnalysisServicesModule`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">No CRUD-side injection of AI internals.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Tool-list query cached per tenant; cache key includes `tenantId`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">No user message content in telemetry; tool resolution emits tool count + tenant ID + timestamp only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">No new feature flags. Use existing capability flag (if any) for fallback gating.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Verify BFF publish-size delta; ≤+5 MB R6 budget per NFR-02.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-01">Conversational primacy — tool list restricts function-calling vocabulary but never prevents conversational responses.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-13">Safety pipeline middleware chain unchanged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-11">Tool list is data-driven via `sprk_analysistool` query with `AvailableInContexts ∋ "Chat"` filter.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-11">Backward compatibility during migration: existing 10 hardcoded chat tools continue to work while migration proceeds.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff-api/chat-tool-resolution</topic>
