  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — chat-agent core cutover + NFR-01 binding + downstream blocker".
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 010 ✅. Update `current-task.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge. Capture baseline publish size.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Inspect `ResolveTools()` Today">
      Open `SprkChatAgentFactory.cs`. Identify the current hardcoded tool list (10 instances). Plan the swap: query → adapter → AIFunction[].
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Data-Driven Resolution">
      Query `sprk_analysistool` rows filtered by tenant + `AvailableInContexts ∋ Chat`. Cache result with `tenantId`-keyed Redis key per ADR-014 (short TTL, e.g. 5 min, since data changes are infrequent). For each row: locate the corresponding `IToolHandler` implementation (via DI keyed lookup; pattern from existing handlers) and wrap via adapter.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Implement Fallback Strategy">
      During migration window, retain a fallback path that returns the hardcoded tool list if the data-driven query returns ZERO tools (defensive). Gate via existing capability flag if one fits; document the choice. NO new feature flags.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Add Conversational-Primacy Test">
      Test asserting: even when data-driven query returns ZERO tools, the chat agent still responds conversationally (NFR-01). Safety pipeline middleware chain still applied (NFR-13).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Add Backward-Compat Test">
      Test asserting: with mocked data-driven query returning the 10 hardcoded tools as rows, the resolved AIFunction[] matches the prior hardcoded list semantically. This validates the migration path.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build + Verify Publish Size">
      `dotnet build` → 0 errors. `dotnet publish -c Release` → measure delta vs baseline; report ≤+5 MB R6 budget.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk each criterion; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check`. Verify ADR-010 / ADR-013 / ADR-014 / ADR-015 / ADR-018 / ADR-029 + NFR-01 / NFR-11 / NFR-13 + FR-11 compliance. Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 011 ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">build, test, publish</tool>
    <tool name="git">stage + commit changes</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__read_query">MCP — verify `sprk_analysistool` queries</tool>
    <tool name="code-review">Quality gate Step 9.5</tool>
